s, and environmentalists, among many others—populate this fascinating chronicle of American tastes and the forces that influence them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCanned tunaxHistoryxUnited States. 0aCanned tunazUnited StatesxHistory. 0aCooking (Tuna) 0aCooking (Tuna). 0aFish as foodxHistoryxUnited States. 0aFish as foodzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aTuna fisheriesxEnvironmental aspectsxHistory. 0aTuna fisheriesxHistory. 0aTuna industryxHistory. 0aTunaxHistoryxUnited States. 0aTunazUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  a20th century america.  a20th century foods.  aamerican culture.  aamerican food.  aamerican history.  aamerican seafood.  aamerican tuna.  achicken of the sea.  acookbooks.  acooking and food.  acritical food topics.  ademise of industry.  adietary trends history.  aeasy to read.  aeducational books.  aengaging.  aenvironmental politics.  afood and politics.  afood culture.  afood industry.  afood lovers.  afood studies.  aforeign policy.  agastronomy.  ahistory of food.  alearning while reading.  anonfiction books.  apopular foods.  apopular seafood.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095415140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954151423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520954151/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles